    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, you're not used to the goblin way of thinking? That's fine! It's just that goblins are the only things that understand how electricity works in this world. Think of your car battery like a goblin's stash of gold coins—it stores energy when you're parked and gives it all at once when you need to start the engine. But the alternator is the goblin's bossy boss who keeps the stash full while you're driving.\n\nHere's the mechanical part, but imagine it's a goblin workshop: The alternator is a spinning machine (like a giant goblin wheel) that uses your engine's movement to generate electricity. It has a rotor that spins inside a stator, creating a magnetic field that pushes electrons around, just like a goblin pushing a boulder up a hill to get it to roll down and power everything. This electricity goes back into your battery to recharge it, so the goblin doesn't have to work too hard.\n\nIf your alternator is shot, it's like the goblin boss has lost their mind and stopped pushing the boulder. You'll notice your lights flicker like a goblin trying to light a fire with a match, your radio cuts out",
